00:00:21.280 --> 00:00:25.200
At the start of the movie, we see a ferry&nbsp;
preparing to leave for its destination.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:29.680
The ferry is packed with the locals, and among&nbsp;
them is Jane, the main character of the movie.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:29.680 --> 00:00:34.080
She is a 15 year old french school girl from&nbsp;
a remote village in Vietnam. Her mother is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:38.560
a school teacher in that village. And she has&nbsp;
two brothers. Her elder brother Pierre is the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:43.440
bully of the house. He acts like the head of the&nbsp;
house and he has his younger brother in control.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:48.640
Paul is just the opposite of Pierre. He easily&nbsp;
gets intimidated by Pierre and is scared of him.

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:53.360
Jane lives in a school hostel in Saigon, and&nbsp;
was there to spend the holidays with her family.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:57.840
But, due to Pierre, Jane isn’t exactly&nbsp;
happy. She doesn’t like him bullying Paul,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:57.840 --> 00:01:02.400
and screams at him. Jane’s mother seeing the&nbsp;
rude behavior of Pierre says nothing to him.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:06.000
Jane says that she only loves Pierre&nbsp;
and doesn’t care about her and Paul.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:10.080
Her mother says she loves all of them&nbsp;
equally, but Jane knows that she is lying.

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:14.160
Despite running the school in the village,&nbsp;
Jane’s family are financially struggling.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:14.160 --> 00:01:17.200
And Pierre being the eldest&nbsp;
male of the house, does nothing.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:20.480
Instead, he steals money from&nbsp;
his mother to smoke opium.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:24.640
Today was the last day of her vacation,&nbsp;
and Jane is returning back to Saigon.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:29.120
Her mother hands her some money and bids her&nbsp;
fare well. She gets to the ferry, and is waiting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:33.920
for it to leave. A vehicle of a rich man also&nbsp;
boards the ferry, and then the ferry starts.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:33.920 --> 00:01:38.400
The owner of the car starts looking at&nbsp;
Jane from his car. He finds her beautiful.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:43.120
So, he steps out to get a clear look.&nbsp;
His name is Tony, a rich chinese man.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:43.120 --> 00:01:48.240
He steps forwards and goes near where Jane&nbsp;
is. He offers her a cigarette. So, it shows&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:53.280
that he clearly doesn’t think that Jane is an&nbsp;
underage girl. Jane kindly declines Tony’s offer&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:58.640
for a smoke. Tony tries to strike a conversation,&nbsp;
but he gets no response from Jane. Then, he&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:58.640 --> 00:02:04.320
compliments Jane on her beauty, and this time Jane&nbsp;
replies. Tony tells Jane that if she doesn’t mind,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:10.240
he can take her to Saigon in his car. Jane agrees&nbsp;
to it. She leaves from the ferry, in Tony’s car.

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:14.880
In the car, Jane notices Tony’s ring, and&nbsp;
she is definitely intrigued by his wealth.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:19.920
Tony asks Jane about her age. Despite her&nbsp;
being 15 years old, Jane lies about her age,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:24.480
and tells Tony that she is 17.&nbsp;
Tony replies that he is 32.&nbsp;

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:29.120
Jane tells him that she studies in a school&nbsp;
in Saigon, but lives in a separate hostel.&nbsp;

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:34.080
Tony tells her about his family. His mother died&nbsp;
10 years ago, and since her death, his father&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:34.080 --> 00:02:39.200
became sad and hasn’t left the house. His father&nbsp;
takes care of the business all from his bed.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:43.520
Tony says that he quite doesn’t understand how&nbsp;
his father could love his mother that much. 
 &nbsp;

