intimacy was growing stronger with every visit.

00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:52.720
One night, Tony tells Jane that his father&nbsp;
wants him to marry the daughter of a rich&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:57.040
chinese businessman. Jane asks him if&nbsp;
he knows that woman. Tony replies that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:57.040 --> 00:05:00.960
he doesn’t know her at all. Jane acts&nbsp;
like this doesn’t concern her at all.

00:05:00.960 --> 00:05:05.360
Jane and Tony, both know that they can’t be&nbsp;
together for ever. So, they try not to take&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:09.840
these things seriously. They’re just focused on&nbsp;
the physical relationship they have going on.

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:15.360
One day, Jane returns to her house on&nbsp;
vacation. But she came there in Tony’s car.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:18.720
So, her mother interrogates her&nbsp;
about who dropped her to their house.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:22.560
Jane replies that it was a rich friend&nbsp;
that they don’t know. But Jane’s mother&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:27.200
shows her a letter from her hostel, which says&nbsp;
that she often spent nights outside the hostel.

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:30.320
Jane doesn’t say anything, and&nbsp;
Pierre starts calling her names,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:30.320 --> 00:05:34.800
and encourages his mother to hit her. But,&nbsp;
her mother doesn’t know what to do and leaves.

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:40.000
At the end of her vacation, Jane takes her family&nbsp;
to meet Tony. Tony acts respectfully towards them,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.480
but they all seem disinterested in him. Tony&nbsp;
begins to tell them about himself, but they’re&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:49.120
all just focused on eating. Jane is aware of&nbsp;
all this, but she doesn't do or say anything,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:53.840
because she doesn’t want her family to know about&nbsp;
her feelings for Tony. She wants her family to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:58.000
think that Tony was just a rich friend,&nbsp;
and not someone she loved or slept with.

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.040
After the dinner, Tony opens&nbsp;
his wallet to pay the bill.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:01.040 --> 00:06:06.000
Jane’s mother is surprised by the amount of money&nbsp;
that Tony has. They leave the restaurant and go to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:11.520
another place. Pierre starts a fight, but Tony&nbsp;
keeps his composure and sits down. Meanwhile,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:14.880
Jane acts unfazed by the behavior&nbsp;
of their family towards Tony.

00:06:14.880 --> 00:06:19.040
She even starts to dance with Paul, and Tony&nbsp;
watches it with almost a tear falling down&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:19.040 --> 00:06:23.920
from his eyes. He realizes that Jane’s family&nbsp;
came to meet him only because of his money.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:27.520
He thinks that Jane too was involved&nbsp;
with him, only because he was rich.

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:30.960
Later that night, Tony takes&nbsp;
Jane back to his bachelor house.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:30.960 --> 00:06:35.600
Jane is nervous because of the way Tony was&nbsp;
treated by her family. Tony comes close to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:40.800
her and slaps her. He thinks that Jane slept with&nbsp;
him not because she liked him, but for his money.

00:06:40.800 --> 00:06:45.360
Tony starts to take his clothes off, and&nbsp;
Jane just lies down without any emotion.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:49.200
That night was different from all the&nbsp;
others they had previously spent together.

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:52.800
Jane, to act like she doesn’t like&nbsp;
him, asks Tony for some money.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:58.000
Tony takes some money out of his wallet, and&nbsp;
throws it down. He seems frustrated by everything.

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:02.560
Jane takes that money and gives it to her mother.&nbsp;
Her mother then talks to the hostel warden,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:05.840
and asks her to let Jane leave&nbsp;
the hostel anytime she wants.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:10.320
Jane’s mother was doing it so Jane could go&nbsp;
meet Tony and take more money from him. She&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:15.200
thinks that Tony is just a rich friend of Jane.&nbsp;
She doesn’t know that Jane is sleeping with him.

00:07:15.200 --> 00:07:20.400
But soon enough, everyone at the school finds&nbsp;
out about Jane and Tony. She becomes an outcast.

00:07:20.400 --> 00:07:25.280
One night, Tony is leaving to meet his father&nbsp;
to talk about his marriage. Before leaving, he&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:25.280 --> 00:07:30.640
gives Jane the ring that belonged to his mother.&nbsp;
Despite everything, he still had feelings for her.

00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:35.040
Tony goes to his father, and tells him that he&nbsp;
doesn’t want to marry the girl that his father&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:39.760
had arranged. He says that he is in love with&nbsp;
Jane. But his father doesn’t allow this idea,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:43.120
and tells him that he has to marry&nbsp;
the girl that he has arranged.

00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:46.960
Tony goes to Jane and tells her about&nbsp;
everything. He says that he loves her,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:46.960 --> 00:07:51.200
but also cannot go against his father, because&nbsp;
he is nothing without his father’s money.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:51.200 --> 00:07:56.720
Tony is in a dilemma, he doesn’t know what to do.&nbsp;
But, Jane tells Tony that she doesn’t love him.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:56.720 --> 00:08:02.240
So, he should marry the girl that his father&nbsp;
wants. Hearing this from Jane, Tony becomes sad.

00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:06.720
Jane takes Tony to their family property.&nbsp;
She tells Tony that when her father died,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:12.080
her mother was lied to by land sellers, and was&nbsp;
sold flood lands. That was how they became poor.

00:08:12.080 --> 00:08:15.280
Jane stays there thinking about the&nbsp;
pain her mother might have suffered.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:18.560
And Tony shares her emotion, but&nbsp;
there is a distance between them.

00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:23.200
The last night of their being together, Tony asks&nbsp;
Jane to tell him that she only slept with him,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:27.920
because of his money. Jane repeats the&nbsp;
exact words that Tony wants her to say.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:27.920 --> 00:08:31.280
Tony wants her to say this to make&nbsp;
it easier for him to forget her.

00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:34.800
Jane tries to get close to him.&nbsp;
But Tony stops her and says that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:34.800 --> 00:08:37.840
he is ashamed of himself for not&nbsp;
being able to take Jane with him.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:37.840 --> 00:08:42.320
He also says that he no longer wants to&nbsp;
sleep with Jane, because she didn’t love him.

00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:46.640
Next day, Jane goes to her house in Tony’s&nbsp;
car. Her mother and brother see the ring&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:46.640 --> 00:08:51.680
that Tony had given her. They ask her why Tony&nbsp;
gave her such an expensive gift. Pierre says&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:51.680 --> 00:08:56.240
that Jane was probably sleeping with Tony, and&nbsp;
that’s why he gave that expensive ring to her.

00:08:56.240 --> 00:09:00.560
To avert their suspicion, Jane throws the&nbsp;
ring and says that she doesn’t care about it.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:00.560 --> 00:09:04.720
But Pierre doesn’t believe her at all.&nbsp;
He slaps her and starts hitting her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:08.240
Paul hears everything, but he is&nbsp;
helpless and can’t do anything.

00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:12.400
After seeing Pieere get violent, his mother&nbsp;
sends him back to France, to join the war,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:12.400 --> 00:09:17.680
to keep her other two children safe. But she is&nbsp;
sad to see him go away, as she loved him the most.

00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.880
Few months later, Jane goes&nbsp;
back to Tony’s bachelor house,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:20.880 --> 00:09:25.520
and finds him completely changed. He was&nbsp;
lifeless, and spent his days smoking.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:25.520 --> 00:09:30.000
Jane asks him when he was getting married.&nbsp;
Tony replies that it was just days later.

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:34.880
And when that day came, Jane went to see the&nbsp;
marriage of Tony and his wife. Tony sees Jane,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:34.880 --> 00:09:39.520
but he quickly averts his eyes. Jane gets&nbsp;
sad as she sees Tony and his wife leave.

00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:44.800
Jane goes to her house. Her family is preparing&nbsp;
to leave Vietnam. Her mother reveals that Tony&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:44.800 --> 00:09:49.840
had paid the debt that Pierre had made in Vietnam,&nbsp;
and he also paid for their trip back to France.

00:09:49.840 --> 00:09:54.480
Before leaving for France, Jane goes back to&nbsp;
Tony’s bachelor house and sits there waiting for&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:54.480 --> 00:09:59.840
him. She hopes that Tony will come to see her one&nbsp;
last time. She waits for hours, but Tony doesn’t&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:59.840 --> 00:10:05.200
show up. So, she leaves the house without getting&nbsp;
to meet Tony, and be with him for the last time.

00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:10.000
As Jane leaves Vietnam, she sees Tony’s car&nbsp;
sitting there, just like when they first met.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:14.560
Tony isn’t visible, but she knows that he is&nbsp;
watching her, and she is watching him too.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:18.480
As the ship started drifting away,&nbsp;
she no longer could see Tony’s car.

00:10:18.480 --> 00:10:22.000
Years go by, and one day, Jane&nbsp;
receives a call from Tony.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:25.600
It has been years since their life&nbsp;
was separated. But Tony tells her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:30.080
